newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: SFE wheat futures track Chicago down.
newsitem.headline: SFE wheat futures track Chicago down.

text.p: Sydney Futures Exchange wheat futures fell on Friday to reflect Chicago's overnight decline.
Market leader January 1998 fell by A$5.00 to A$173.00 a tonne on the trade compared with the previous settlement close. Thirteen lots changed hands.
Settlement prices of the two nearest-term contracts stayed firm but most other settlement prices fell by A$3.50.

The market was tracking Chicago, with El Nino drought scares not a factor in Friday's market. Overnight rain in in the south of Australia's east-side could open a spread between Sydney and Chicago wheat, a broker said.
Chicago wheat futures fell by a range of three to 11-1/2 US cents a bushel on Thursday on a higher USDA U.S. production forecast.
